The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Kathmandu, June 7 (PTI): Hundreds of Maoists today forcibly shut down Hindustan Unilevers plant in Nepal protesting the alleged encroachment of Nepalese territory by Indian forces.           
	The Tamang Rashtriya Mukti Morcha also forcibly closed shops and vandalised vehicles in Makawanpur district, where the plant is located.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): The president of Mafatlal Luxury, Sheetal Mafatlal, was detained at Mumbai international airport on Sunday for allegedly carrying undisclosed jewellery and diamonds worth several lakhs, customs officials said. Mafatlal was intercepted following a tip-off.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The railways will launch another number  138  to provide additional information. Passengers can ask for information about routes and schedules at different stations, IRCTC managing director Rakesh Tandon said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has pulled up the National Human Rights Commission for acting without sanction of law while commuting a death sentence. The panel can only probe human rights violation cases, the court said.                                                                                                                           
